Heat oil in a large skillet over medium high heat. Add chicken; cook, stirring occasionally, for 4 to 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Stir in water and seasoning mix. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cook, stirring occasionally, for 4 to 5 minutes or until mixture is thickened. FILL taco shells with chicken mixture. Top with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and taco sauce.